  wikipedia salon website from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from salon media group inc jump to navigation search this article may require copy editing for grammar style cohesion tone or spelling you can assist by editing it may  learn how and when to remove this template message salon type of site news website available in english owner salon media group inc created by david talbot editor andrew ohehir key people jordan hoffner ceo website saloncom alexa rank  november update commercial yes registration optional launched april    years ago  current status online oclc  salon is an american news and opinion website created by david talbot in  the site is owned by salon media group otcqb slnm it focuses on us politics culture and current events from a politically progressive or leftwing perspective salons headquarters is located at  market street san francisco california as of june  its editorinchief is david daley after previous editorinchief kerry lauerman stepped down to partner with larer ventures on a new startup lauermans predecessor joan walsh stepped down from that position in november  but remained as editor at large contents  content and coverage  staff and contributors  history  business model and operations  controversy  references  external links content and coverage salon covers a variety of topics these include reviews and articles about books films and music articles about modern life including friendships human sexual behavior and relationships and reviews and articles about technology with a particular focus on the free and opensource software foss movement according to the senior contributing writer for the american journalism review paul farhi salon offers provocative if predictably liberal political commentary and lots of sex in  salon launched the interactive initiative open salon a social content siteblog network for its readers originally a curated site with some of its content being featured on salon it fell into editorial neglect and was closed in march  responding to the question how far do you go with the tabloid sensibility to get readers former saloncom editorinchief david talbot said is salon more tabloidlike yeah weve made no secret of that ive said all along that our formula here is that were a smart tabloid if by tabloid what you mean is youre trying to reach a popular audience trying to write topics that are viscerally important to a readership whether its the story about the mother in houston who drowned her five children or the story on the missing intern in washington chandra levy staff and contributors alex pareene who wrote about politics for salon in new york in  regular contributors include the politicalopinion writers amanda marcotte scott eric kaufman heather digby parton and sean illing critic andrew ohehir popculture columnist mary elizabeth williamscitation needed david talbot founded salon and became its original editorinchief he has served several stints as ceo most recently replacing richard gingras who left to join google as head of news products in july  as of may  the companys ceo is jordan hoffner history salon was created by former san francisco examiner staff who had departed the newspaper seeking to explore the potential of the web especially in the wake of the newspaper strike that had occurred in november  the magazine was founded by the examiners former arts and features editor david talbot and launched in november  in its early days readers noticed a specifically northern california flavor in an interview in  talbott agreed we swim in the soup of san francisco there are a lot of odd fish weve plucked out of the bay here and it gives us some of that left coast weird coast style time magazine named it one of the best web site of  salon purchased the virtual community the well in april  and made its initial public offering ipo of saloncom on the nasdaq stock exchange on june  of that year subsequently for the month october  nielsennetratings reported that salon had over  million users salon premium a paytoview online content subscription was introduced on april   the service signed over  subscribers and staved off discontinuation of services however less than two years later in november  the company announced it had accumulated cash and noncash losses of  million and by february  it was having difficulty paying its rent and made an appeal for donations to keep the company running frontpage design in  on october   michael odonnell the chief executive and president of salon media group said he was leaving the company after seven years because it was time for a change when he left saloncom had accrued  million in losses since its inception and its stock traded for ¢ on the otc bulletin board david talbot salons chairman and editorinchief at the time became the new chief executive elizabeth betsy hambrecht then salons chief financial officer became the president in july  salon launched open salon a social content site and curated blog network it was nominated for a  national magazine award in the category best interactive feature on march   salon announced it would be closing open salon after six years of hosting a community of writers and bloggers on june   salon closed its online chat board table talk without stating an official reason for ending that section of the site on july   salon announced that it will be featuring content from mondoweiss in september  salon media group sold the well to the group of members business model and operations salon has been unprofitable through its entire history since  the company has been dependent on ongoing cash injections from board chairman john warnock and william hambrecht father of former salon ceo elizabeth hambrecht during the nine months ended december   these cash contributions amounted to  million compared to revenue in the same period of  million aspects of the saloncom site offerings ordered by advancing date free content around  new articles posted perday revenues wholly derived from inpage advertisements perday new content was reduced for a time salon premium subscription approximately  percent of new content was made available to subscribers only other subscription benefits included free magazines and adfree viewing larger more conspicuous ad units introduced for nonsubscribers a hybrid subscription model readers now can read content by viewing a second full screen advertisement to earn a day pass or gain access by subscribing to salon premium salon core after salon premium subscriptions declined from about  to  it was rebranded in  as salon core subscriptions featuring a different mix of benefits controversy in march  while otto warmbier was imprisoned in north korea the site posted an article about warmbier called this might be america’s biggest idiot frat boy meet the uva student who thought he could pull a prank in north korea after warmbiers death the article was subsequently removed andrew ohehir the executive editor of salon said that the article was based on the opinions of larry wilmore references  saloncom site overview alexa internet retrieved august     saloncom whois dns  domain info  domaintools whois retrieved    the fall of saloncom politico  march    the new salon – very different from the old salon politico media retrieved    note to liberal media outlets opposition to syrian refugees is not a fringe position washington post retrieved    kurtz howard  salon’s clickbait strategy the phantom fight against fox news fox news retrieved    form q securities and exchange commission   bloomgardensmoke kara june   kerry lauerman is leaving salon dave daley named interim editor in chief the new york observer   marr dave february   salon editor david daley first willsongrady digital media fellow grady college   walsh joan  november  im not leaving salon salon archived from the original on december   retrieved  december    about salon salon   farhi paul march  can salon make it ajrarchiveorg american journalism review ret